li>  <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Save&nbsp;<a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/git/git/master/contrib/completion/git-completion.bash" target="_blank" style="box-sizing: border-box; background: transparent;" title=""><font color="#2A2A2A">this file</font></a>&nbsp;in your home directory with the name&nbsp;<font color="#24678D">git-completion.bash</font> </li>  <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Save&nbsp;<a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/git/git/master/contrib/completion/git-prompt.sh" target="_blank" style="box-sizing: border-box; background: transparent;" title=""><font color="#2A2A2A">this file</font></a>&nbsp;in your home directory with the name&nbsp;<font color="#24678D">git-prompt.sh</font> </li>  <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Also download <a href="http://nejahi.com/uploads/bash_profile" title="">this file</a> to your home directory and rename it to <font color="#24678D">.bash_profile</font> <font color="#2A2A2A">( please don't forgot about the dot )</font> </li>  <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">If you already have a file in your home directory named .bash_profile, copy the content and paste it at the bottom of&nbsp;.bash_profile.</li>  <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Run the following Git configuration commands. The first one will need to be modified if you are using a text editor other than Sublime, or if Sublime is installed in another location for you</li> </ul> </div>  <div> <div id="880659829706281970" align="left" style="width: 100%; overflow-y: hidden;" class="wcustomhtml"> <pre class="prettyprint"> git config --global core.editor "'C:/Program Files/Sublime Text 2/sublime_text.exe' -n -w" git config --global push.default upstream git config --global merge.conflictstyle diff3 </pre> </div> </div>  <div> <div id="322677795714826832" align="left" style="width: 100%; overflow-y: hidden;" class="wcustomhtml"> <!--wp code prettify-->     <!--//wp code prettify--> </div> </div> ]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><!